        "id": "1e90e295-ed4d-4fa0-b919-b24f368263b8",
        "text": "There are many differences in the way cases are reviewed. It is questionable that the results would be different if cases were conducted under the differing approaches; in fact no statistics exist that can show whether or not these systems would come to the same results. However, these approaches are often a matter of national pride and there are opinions amongst jurists about the merits of the differing approaches and their drawbacks as well - [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adversarial_Law#Comparisons_with_the_inquisitorial_approach wikipedia]"
