      "item": {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "id": "a2271b8c-c8d0-430c-b250-4034c28f5e24",
        "text": "Proponents of the adversarial system often argue that the system is more fair and less prone to abuse than the inquisitional approach, because it allows less room for the state to be biased against the defendant. It also allows most private litigants to settle their disputes in an amicable manner through discovery and pre-trial settlements in which non-contested facts are agreed upon and not dealt with during the trial process."
      },
      "after": "1e90e295-ed4d-4fa0-b919-b24f368263b8",
      "id": "a2271b8c-c8d0-430c-b250-4034c28f5e24",
      "date": 1469534536869
